<br>
Where it pisses me off is on the quest items. Stuff (like the infamous shackles) that has nothing to do with needing to get a group of the appropriate level to handle it; it's just a matter of slaughtering things to get the much-lower-level rare thing to spawn, and by the time you finally manage to get it to spawn, it's trivial. And then people say, &quot;Oh well, that's part of the tradeoff, you just can't do all the quests you want to,&quot; well screw that. This is (to use the oft-repeated cliche) EverQUEST, and I'd like to do QUESTS with my character on this, the roleplaying server, because it is in character for him to want to accomplish these things. The Iksar quest lines in particular don't even return all that great of rewards, but it's a matter of RP, cultural pride in wielding them. And currently the only way to do them is to get high level friends to babysit you (so they kill the higher stuff so you don't get exp from it and outlevel the thing you're camping), or constantly delevel yourself to stay in that tiny tiny window where you can kill the placeholders and still get exp from the quest mob.<br>
<br>
TLC forces micromanagement of exp in order to do quests. It REQUIRES you to go to spoiler sites and carefully plan out your character's &quot;life.&quot; Yeah. That's really in the spirit of RP. Heaven forbid you actually try to do some quests in order, in actual RP fashion, one step at a time, because the TLC will screw you. (Case in point: The 2nd Iksar Shaman quests requires you to kill a rare level 10ish mob, which is surrounded by level 17ish placeholders. If you somehow manage to survive this, the 3rd quest then tells you to go kill a level 7 mob. Solution: do the quests out of order - which makes no RP sense since your character wouldn't even be assigned the 3rd quest until he did the 2nd - &quot;hire a newbie&quot; to go hunt the level 7 mob for you, if you're stunningly lucky to find a newbie who doesn't mind wasting several hours/days hunting in an area that otherwise holds nothing of interest for him, or delevel. Whee.)<br>
<br>
TLC in dungeons, on loot drops, is cool and fine, and that's where the farming is gonna happen, if it's gonna happen at all, so that's where it's &quot;needed.&quot; TLC server-wide, in a blanket application that doesn't take into consideration the difficulty level a lot of quests were designed for, is just lame.<br>
<br>
Puppy, thinking maybe he just shouldn't have played an Iksar. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utukka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tukka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/27/01 11:17:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=740.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.atlantic.net/~tukka/hand.gif height=42 width=42></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Some of this Trivial Loot Code sucks.</span><hr size=1> It sounds like you Iksars have a very legitimate complaint about how TLC is making your quests virtually impossible.  What EVERYBODY needs to do is report these impossible/almost impossible quests to Verant via feedback or to our server GM so that they can be adjusted, whenever you encounter and verify them.  The solution would be as simple as removing the magic/lore properties from the quest items that are nigh impossible to obtain thanks to TLC.<br>
