<br>
So, forget the 'TLC prevents farming' idea; it doesn't. It just means you do your farming a little earlier in some cases. But really, if making money is the goal, then zipping to 60 is, as always, the way to go, since the attainable loot at 60 is still vastly superior to anything you can get at lower levels and, on this server, it's most likely tradeable too.<br>
<br>
The TLC has only inconvenienced me a few times, primarily related to quests for things on low-to-medium level mobs. Having gotten what I need now, it doesn't bother me at all anymore. I realize it does in general screw over the many to 'get' the few (and doesn't even succeed in the latter), but at least I know *I* am no longer one of the many who will get shafted by the TLC but shouldn't, nor am I one of the few who SHOULD get shafted. I have escaped. /cheer<br>
<br>
As for sending in reports trying to get things fixed: um, be serious. The odds of any of this stuff being addressed in any remotely reasonable timeframe is so low that I sure wouldn't hold my breath. These problems exist on ONE SERVER. They have problems unfixed from the original EQ, from Kunark, from Velious, and now (I'm sure) from Luclin that affect ALL servers. Any FV-specific problems will be so far down the 'to do' list that you can basically forget about them ever being addressed. I have personally reported some of these issues almost two months ago, and there is no sign that any fix is even being considered. Hell, when people were leveling past 20 after EQ was released, it took *months*, until some folks were 50th, before they added research into the game, thus allowing mage pets higher than 20th level. Ever see mages in their 40s with L20 pets? It's pretty rough. And that WAS a problem that affected all servers. So, if you have a problem with how the TLC is affecting you, then your only realistic choices are to work around it if you can (and I realize many you simply cannot work around), or just forget the quest.<br>
<br>
And yes, I carefully planned out my character's leveling. Even so, I did miss a few things on the way. It seemed bizarre to me to HAVE to plan things out like that, but I did it. I mean, how un-RP can you get than knowing fairly precisely what your destiny is (and must be) for the next few weeks, in such specificity?<br>
<br>
I am deeply sorry for those of you who will ultimately be screwed by the TLC and will have no real recourse except the 'report and pray' option. But at least you can rest happy knowing that while you are being screwed hard, at least the powerlevelers and uberguys will be enduring the same hardship. Oh wait, no they won't, because they have the means to bypass the TLC, and you don't. Welp, guess there is no consolation for the many innocent who will suffer, whereas the guilty few walk away laughing en route to the next farm.<br>
<br>
C'est la vie.<br>
